records.addlTxt:
Defendant Arthur L Grover in court with attorney Jamie Francis Cimpl-Wiemer.  Ronald Dague appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  

Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Defendant sentenced to serve 6 MONTHS in the House of Correction with credit for 119 days time served.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 1 YEAR.
Conditions:  
*  Continue treatment at the Wisconsin Resource Center;
*  AODA assessment/treatment deemed appropriate;
*  Mental health assessment/treatment deemed appropriate;
*  Pay restitution in the amount of $700.00 to Bikesmiths - 2865 N Murray Avenue, Milwaukee, WI  53211;
*  Court will waive any costs and surcharges that can be waived;  Court ordered all other mandatory costs and surcharges to be paid during the term of probation or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.
